<!-- 03 — TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Makes Hestan Different — And How Each System Fails</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Hestan's products are engineered with restaurant-kitchen mindset applied to residential installation. The failure modes reflect that engineering.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Trellis Burner™ Geometry</strong> — The trellis pattern creates more contact points between flame and cooking surface than a standard tube burner, delivering more even heat coverage. The same geometry accumulates grease in the trellis channels differently than tube burners. Proper Trellis Burner cleaning requires specific brushing technique — improper cleaning pushes debris into the burner ports. We clean and inspect the Trellis Burner as a complete assembly, not just the igniter.</li>
        <li><strong>Ceramic Infrared Top Burner</strong> — The 12,000–18,000 BTU ceramic infrared burner for searing and finishing runs at far higher surface temperatures than standard burners. Thermal shock — rapid temperature cycling — is the primary failure mechanism for the ceramic element. We inspect the ceramic for micro-fractures before they become complete failures during service calls.</li>
        <li><strong>Campania Pizza Oven High-Temp Circuit</strong> — The Campania operates at up to 700°F — temperatures that stress every component of the gas circuit differently than a standard grill. The igniter system must generate a spark in a high-temperature environment where the ceramic tip degrades faster than at standard outdoor cooking temperatures. We use high-temp-rated OEM Campania igniters on every Campania service call.</li>
        <li><strong>Horizon Hood™ Spring System</strong> — The Hestan grill's Horizon Hood uses spring-assisted hinges designed to hold at any desired height without swinging. When the spring loses tension, the hood falls closed or won't hold its position. Spring replacement is model-specific — we carry OEM Hestan Horizon Hood spring assemblies.</li>
        <li><strong>Indoor NanoeShield™ Coating</strong> — Hestan's proprietary antimicrobial coating on indoor appliance interiors requires specific cleaning protocols during service. Standard oven cleaning chemicals damage the NanoeShield™ surface. We use only coating-compatible cleaning agents during interior service work.</li>
        <li><strong>Motion-Activated Under-Hood Lighting</strong> — Hestan grills include motion-activated LED lighting that illuminates the cooking surface when the hood opens. LED driver failure is the most common lighting system fault. We carry replacement LED assemblies for current Hestan grill models.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🍕 Campania Pizza Oven — Why It's a Specialty</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">The Hestan Campania is a gas-fired pizza oven with a ceramic deck and dome designed to reach 700°F — temperatures that create service requirements completely unlike a standard outdoor grill. The gas circuit is rated for this temperature range; standard grill gas components are not interchangeable. The ceramic deck needs professional assessment after any unusual event (extreme temperature cycling, thermal shock from rain). We service the Campania as a distinct product, not as a grill variant.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a150a; border-color:#2a7a2a; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#5abf5a">🏭 Made in Anaheim — Parts Speed</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Hestan's Anaheim manufacturing means OEM parts for outdoor models typically arrive same-day or next-day in the LA market. For premium European brands, specialty parts can take a week. When we book a Hestan outdoor service call, we usually have the most common parts on the truck already — and any specialty component arrives before the customer notices a delay.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Hestan Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Trellis Burner™ Not Igniting</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Igniter failure or trellis channel blockage. The trellis geometry accumulates grease in channels that standard tube burners don't have — a full Trellis Burner clean is step one before replacing the igniter. Coastal LA properties add salt air corrosion to the ceramic igniter tip as a secondary cause. We clean first, replace only what's actually failed.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-outdoor">Outdoor</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍕 Campania Pizza Oven Won't Reach Temperature</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Gas pressure fault, igniter degradation in the high-temperature environment, or ventilation restriction reducing oxygen supply to the dome. The Campania's 700°F operating temperature degrades igniters faster than standard grill temperatures. High-temp OEM igniters are required — standard grill igniters fail rapidly at Campania temperatures.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-pizza">Campania</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌊 Coastal Valve Corrosion</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Salt air corrosion on gas valve stems — the valve begins to stick or close partially, causing uneven flame or no-light conditions. This is the most common Hestan outdoor failure in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach. Annual anti-corrosion treatment on valve stems prevents it. Once it occurs, valve replacement with OEM Hestan parts restores full function.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-coastal">Coastal LA</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔆 Horizon Hood™ Won't Stay Up</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Horizon Hood spring tension loss — the spring-assisted hinge loses its calibration over time, causing the hood to fall closed or fail to hold position. Spring replacement is model-specific (different spring rates for different hood sizes). We replace the full spring assembly rather than attempting to re-tension the existing spring.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-outdoor">Outdoor</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Indoor Range Igniter Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">High-BTU indoor range igniters degrade faster than standard residential burners — the same thermal cycling stress we see on Wolf and DCS ranges. Hestan indoor ranges use sealed burners where grease accumulation around the igniter well can contribute to failure. We clean the burner well and replace with OEM Hestan igniters.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💡 Under-Hood Motion Lighting Dead</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">LED driver board failure — the motion-activated lighting system's LED driver fails independently of the main grill electronics. The motion sensor sometimes fails separately from the LED array itself. We test both the driver and the sensor before ordering parts — often it's the driver only, which is less expensive than the full lighting assembly.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

