        <div class="faq-q">What is the Trellis Burner™ and how does it fail?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">The Trellis Burner™ is Hestan's patented grill burner — a trellis-shaped stainless steel configuration delivering 25,000 BTUs with more even heat distribution than tube burners. The trellis geometry accumulates grease in channels that tube burners don't have. We clean the full trellis assembly before replacing any igniter — many Trellis Burner failures are blockage, not component failure.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Where is Hestan made?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Hestan grills are manufactured in Anaheim, California — about 30 miles from Los Angeles. Hestan cuts its own steel, fabricates grates, and laser-cuts components in-house. This makes Hestan the only major luxury grill brand made in the United States. OEM parts for Hestan outdoor products move fast through the LA supply chain as a result.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How often should Hestan outdoor grills be serviced in LA?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Annually for all LA properties; twice per year for coastal locations (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Manhattan Beach, Santa Monica). Annual service includes Trellis Burner™ full clean, igniter inspection, valve stem anti-corrosion treatment, Horizon Hood™ spring check, and lighting test. Coastal properties also get marine anti-corrosion treatment on all accessible metal surfaces. This prevents the majority of outdoor failures we're called for.</div>
